<br>
I decided that the Wizard’s specialty in dealing out massive damage would be a boon on raids; however, now I am hearing that Wizard’s are going to be the masters of transportation?  Does this mean that the class is going away from its alleged prowess in combat?  Oh, when I think of all of the statistics involved in making an informed choice about a class my head starts to ache.<br>
<br>
Evilhugs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Jule Cuddlywitch<br>
Level 34 Wizard<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulenaddaranatar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lenaddar Anatar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/11/01 5:32:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I am NOT a Taxi *pout*</span><hr size=1> First of all this community in general seems to forget that a few months ago the general feeling was that &quot;push&quot; spells would be a great addition to the class. After using them a few times. Not being bugged much at all for Translocates, etc. I can say that I freely agree and actually LIKE these spells - alot. <br>
<br>
As for Verant and the dread vision - get over it. No where have I read that the role of Wizards is getting a complete make over. This is an addition not a redefinition of the class. Don't go overboard on this. Frankly, at 34 you haven't even begun to see the true power of the class. There are so many important levels for you yet to see this its almost shamefull.<br>
<br>
Where Translocates really come to shine and shine well are after Uber-raids. Yeah, you might be in a guild (at this point with uber big raids your not often going to just go on pick up groups - too dicey to risk it with folks you don't have a deep personal contact with but I have done pick-ups for Trak, etc). You can have everyone group up with the few druids that will bother showing up as back-up healers and port them out but its so much more convienient just to translocate Tanks back to cities (little to no travel for them), and others to thier desired destinations. Often times I get clerics outside of Seb, etc that want to go to Dreadlands, GF or NK (why? I have no idea). This saves everyone involved A TON of zoning, fartin' around and generally wasting time. I only wish there was one close to Freeport as that would about make it about perfect for me. <br>
<br>
The above has been my experience. Yes, I grant you that having 2750 mana makes these spells allows me to burn through alot spells before LOM/OOM and that when you first get access to these spells 225 mana is going to seem pretty killer. I grant you all that - really do.<br>
<br>
Basiclly (sp), your not gonna get a ton of new ultra-damage spells from verant. They did that once and the Wizard community was hated, detested and feared because we could KS anyone, anytime, anywhere. Think of this as more of safe alternative to becomming less usefull than a druid at times. Verant will probably do more things like this in the future to make Wizards &quot;More group friendly&quot;. Also, one of the common complaints from Wizards since Kunark's release.<br>
<br>
Wait and see before you throw in the towel on this one.<br>
<br>
